snippet.textDisplay:
I have interesting story regards static electricity and ball lightning. I knew a Canadian flight engineer who had literally thousands hours logged on C-130 Hercules heavy air transport.
He said once over Mediterranean Ocean the plane was empty of cargo and climbing to avoid huge electrical storm. The loadmaster awoken him as it was a very long flight and told him he has a potentially dangerous situation. There was a "bowling ball of flames" rolling around the floorplates the loadmaster had CO2 extinguisher about a foot from it. He knew the CO2 would probably conduct the electricity and told him to put it down. He told the aircraft commander go into shallow climb. The strange bowling ball rolled up the back ramp and at the peak near the tail it blew a hole in the very end of tail upon exiting the airframe. They declared airborne emergency landed Sardinia for shutdown and repairs.
Jerry said this strange event was brought on my empty cargo hold and static electricity from rotary inverters compounded by electrical storm.
Once the aircraft was upgraded to solid state inverters these occurences virtually disappeared.

snippet.textDisplay:
1.) Static electricity is a thing (when I was about five or so, I was terrified by sparks in my bed at night whenever I moved, and my mom dismissed it as a child's imagination, I was terrified to go to bed every night for years until I learned about static electricity).

2.) Farts are a thing (ever see someone light their farts?)

3.) Combustible clothing is a thing (spark, plus methane cloud, plus combustible material = spontaneous human combustion).
